{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "But any model trained on synthetic data must be explicitly declared and can only be used for research purposes and preliminary model exploration.In this paper we propose a method based on ChatGPT to generate medical narratives in German describing the status of imaginary patients based on a distribution of diseases and comorbidities in a real patient cohort.",
    "Thus, any other patient information, recorded in the health record, is required as input data.",
    "The generated medical narratives are then automatically annotated, using information about the diseases and comorbidities employed to generate the narrative.",
    "This is done to train tools for Named Entity Recognition (NER).",
    "The main advantage of using ChatGPT in this scenario is that several tests have proved the quality of the medical texts that it generates [6]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
